        <!-- ===== NOTES ===== -->
        <mxCell id="notes" value="Notes&#10;&#10;• Cardinality: '1' = exactly one · 'many' = zero-to-many · crow's foot indicates the 'many' side&#10;• Yellow tables = audit / compliance critical (Decision_Rationale, ClaimVendorAssignment)&#10;• Purple tables = pool entities used by Assignment Engines (Adjuster, Vendor)&#10;• Blue tables = core claim domain (Policy, Claim, Document, Communication)&#10;• Highlighted column on Claim (loss_type_details) = JSON pattern that absorbs the 11 loss-type-specific schemas in one column&#10;&#10;Schema name format reminder&#10;All technical column names in Dataverse are prefixed gbx_ (e.g. 'holder_name' → gbx_holder_name).&#10;The display names shown here are what users see in forms, Power BI, and exports.&#10;The gbx_ prefix is only visible to developers writing flow expressions or Web API URLs.&#10;Full schema with both physical + logical names: docs/schema/glassbox_schema.csv" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fffbeb;strokeColor=#d97706;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingTop=10;fontSize=11;fontColor=#92400e" vertex="1" parent="1">
